{"session_id":"svc-1778777318398767805","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-14T16:48:39.291743418Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-helix-f063d395-20260514T164819-97bc412b","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"helix-f063d395\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eDocument HELIX\u0026#39;s artifact-type schema as an open, substrate-neutral spec\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nHELIX defines a catalog of artifact types (Vision, PRD, FEAT, US, ADR, SD, TD, TP, deploy and iterate outputs) with type-level metadata (meta.yml) and instance-level frontmatter (the ddx: block). Today this schema is implicit — it lives in the union of meta.yml files, template frontmatters, and what DDx\u0026#39;s artifacttypes loader happens to consume. There is no canonical document a non-DDx substrate could read to implement HELIX compliantly.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Scope: write a substrate-neutral schema spec (location: workflows/artifact-schema.md or similar) that defines:\u0026#xA;1. The artifact-type metadata shape (meta.yml) — every field, what it means, which are required.\u0026#xA;2. The instance frontmatter shape (the ddx: block in markdown artifacts) — fields, semantics, the depends_on graph model.\u0026#xA;3. The conventions HELIX assumes (ID naming, directory layout, phase progression).\u0026#xA;4. Which fields each known consumer reads — DDx today as the reference implementation; future substrates as they appear.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Ratify the ddx: namespace as the open frontmatter schema HELIX adopts (not as a DDx-coupling but as the shared schema DDx ships and HELIX consumes). Future substrates are encouraged to read the same shape.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;This is a documentation bead, not a code change. Its output is the spec other consumers and contributors read.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\nworkflows/artifact-schema.md (or equivalent) exists. It defines meta.yml fields, instance ddx: frontmatter fields, ID and directory conventions, and a consumer table. The doc treats DDx as one (reference) consumer, not as the schema authority. A second consumer (manual operation, a Databricks substrate experiment, etc.) could in principle be built from the spec alone.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\nPromoted: this is the substrate-neutral artifact schema spec non-DDx consumers need.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ehelix, phase:design, kind:spec, area:artifacts, area:workflow\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"helix-f9207605\" spec-id=\"FEAT-008\" base-rev=\"acd3f271a6c364b892dc10425965963027f53ab7\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-008\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-008-artifact-template-quality.md\"\u003eFeature Specification: FEAT-008 — Artifact Template Quality and Completeness\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260514T164819-97bc412b","base_rev":"acd3f271a6c364b892dc10425965963027f53ab7","bead_id":"helix-f063d395","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b","correlation_id":"helix-f063d395:20260514T164819-97bc412b","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260514T164819-97bc412b/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"6c2e5d52aa3009baeb6f2966236997b5e411f41830a08d35ec6a468187e7b7bd","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-cb5b5ef6","worker_id":""}}}
